<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features: Change Profile" role="TOPIC">
  <title>Change Profile</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=System Features: Change Profile" id="BCP"
           role="TOPIC">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">This module has just one function on the System Features
    menu, called <emphasis role="bold">Change Profile</emphasis>. All users
    can use the <application moreinfo="none">Change Profile</application>
    module to view and update their language and password. No particular
    jurisdiction is required to use this feature.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When you click this function, you are presented with a
    form to update your profile.</para>
</section>
    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Change Profile - Navigation</title>

      <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the Change Profile function, from the
      home page, select System Features, then select Change Profile from the
      side navigation menu. Alternatively, select the <emphasis>Manage
      Profile</emphasis> link from the top right of the banner.</para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Change Profile</title>

      <para>When the Change Profile (or Manage Profile) function is selected,
      the Change User Profile page is displayed.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">After entering your changes, click <emphasis
      role="bold">Save</emphasis> at the bottom of the form. When the password
      is changed, the password expiry date is computed and stored, and the
      invalid login attempts counter is reset. Depending on the system
      parameters, the new password may be checked against previously used
      passwords, and may be rejected. This prevents the same password from
      being used, and increases overall security.</para>

